<h2>Solar Incentives in Sacramento</h2>
<p>Sacramento residents have access to several valuable solar incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost, including equipment and installation, and remains at this rate through 2032. California offers additional state-level incentives, including the California Solar Initiative and property tax exemptions for solar installations, meaning your home's increased value from solar panels won't result in higher property taxes. SMUD provides net energy metering (NEM) that credits customers at retail rates for excess solar electricity fed back into the grid, plus time-of-use rates that can maximize savings when solar production is highest. Additionally, Sacramento County occasionally offers local rebate programs, and financing options like PACE (Property Assessed Clean Energy) loans allow homeowners to pay for solar installations through their property tax bills over 15-20 years.</p>

