<p>When selecting a solar installer in Sacramento, prioritize companies with proper California State License Board (CSLB) licensing, specifically the C-46 Solar Contractor license, and verification through SMUD's approved contractor network. Look for installers with at least 5 years of experience specifically in Sacramento's climate and utility requirements, as they'll understand local permitting processes, SMUD interconnection procedures, and optimal panel positioning for Sacramento's sun patterns. Top-tier companies should offer comprehensive warranties including 20-25 year equipment warranties, 10-year workmanship guarantees, and ongoing monitoring services. Verify the company's Better Business Bureau rating, read recent customer reviews focusing on post-installation support, and ensure they provide detailed energy production estimates based on your home's specific orientation and Sacramento's solar irradiance data. The best Sacramento solar companies will also handle all permitting, SMUD interconnection paperwork, and coordinate inspections, making the process seamless for homeowners.</p>

